title: yusuf_dikec
body:
[b]Yusuf Dikeç[/b] (born on January 1, 1973) is a Turkish sport shooter and multiple-times world champion who participated in the [[2024 Summer Olympics]].

He has gained [[meme]]tic fame for winning a silver medal in the mixed 10-m air pistol shooting event while wearing only [[casual]] clothing and without using special [[olympic shooting glasses]], also his seeming nonchalance, aiming and shooting with one hand on the gun and the other in his pocket, most probably due to him being a former police officer and retired soldier. Because of this, he is known in Japan as the "free-to-play uncle" (無課金おじさん, [i]Mukakin oji-san[/i]) and helped spawned a [[yusuf dikec (meme)|meme imitating his shooting stance]]. He's also a cat person, as revealed by "his Instagram":[https://www.instagram.com/p/Ck_JvBWoyMN].

* !asset #22529009

h4. See Also
* [[Kim Yeji]]

h4.External links
* "Wikipedia article":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yusuf_Dikeç]

title: asajj_ventress
body: Asajj Ventress (/əˈsɑːʒ ˈvɛntrəs/) is a character in the [[Star Wars]] franchise created by [[George Lucas]]. She was introduced in Genndy Tartakovsky's 2003 animated series [[Star Wars: Clone Wars]] (voiced by Grey DeLisle). The character later appeared in the 2008 animated film [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]], the 2008 television series of the same name, and the 2021 Disney+ series [[Star Wars: The Bad Batch]] (voiced by Nika Futterman)

title: asta_(honkai:_star_rail)
body:
A playable character in [[Honkai: Star Rail]].

She is the inquisitive lead astronomy researcher responsible for handling the Herta Space Station's affairs, including managing the staff and responding to the Intelligentsia Guild. Voiced by [[Akasaki Chinatsu]]. 

She is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[pink hair]] with a golden [[hairclip]], [[purple eyes]], and [[medium breasts]]. Her default outfit consists of a [[sleeveless]] [[white shirt]], [[black skirt|black]] [[pleated skirt]], [[black bow|black]] [[bowtie]], [[black choker]], [[lanyard]] with her [[ID card]], [[off shoulder]] [[white jacket]], single [[thigh strap]] on her right leg, and [[black footwear|black]] [[high heels]]. 

h4. Appearance
* !post #7689951: Splash art

h4. Profile
[expand]
A fiercely inquisite and energetic young girl, she is the lead Researcher of Herta Space Station.

Whether it is managing opinionated staff, or courteously but firmly responding to the Intelligentsia Guild, Asta handles it all effortlessly.

After all... Commanding a space station is much easier than taking over a company!
[/expand]

title: hook_(honkai:_star_rail)
body:
A playable character in [[Honkai: Star Rail]].

The self-proclaimed boss of The Moles adventure squad. She views life as an opportunity for freedom and countless adventures. Voiced by [[Tokui Sora]]. 

She is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] tied into [[twintails]], and [[yellow eyes]]. Her default outfit consists of a [[white hat|white]] [[ushanka]], [[black coat|black]] [[fur-trimmed coat]], [[yellow shirt]], [[black gloves]], [[black shorts]], [[single knee pad]] on her left, and [[black footwear|black]] [[boots]]. 

h4. Appearance
* !post #7690007: Splash art

h4. Profile
[expand]
"Who am I? Heh, I'm the boss around here, you can call me... Pitch-Dark Hook the Great!"

Don't underestimate her, she's the boss of The Moles adventure squad! If you stand out on your adventure, maybe Pitch-Dark Hook the Great will invite you to join The Moles. You'll have to find out for yourself what kind of experience that would be~
[/expand]

title: equinox_(racehorse)
body:
[tn]Named after the time of the year when day and night are the same length. Alludes to the contrast between the names of his sire and dam (Black & White).[/tn]
Japanese [[horse|racehorse]]. Sired by [[Kitasan Black (racehorse)|]] and foaled by Chateau Blanche (by [[King Halo (racehorse)|]]).

A brown horse with a stocking on his right back leg and a wide blaze marking.

He gained fame, initially, for coming in second place for both the Satsuki-sho (to [[Geoglyph (racehorse)|]]) and the [[Tokyo Yushun]] (to [[Do Deuce (racehorse)|]]), before turning to the 2022 Autumn Tenno-sho, where he covered and overtook runner [[Panthalassa (racehorse)|]]'s 15 to 20 lengths lead, earning him his first GI title. Equinox then went on to win the 2022 [[Arima Kinen]] as well as the 2023 Dubai Sheema Classic in his overseas stint. Afterwards, he won the 2023 [[Takarazuka Kinen]] by a neck, almost losing to Through Seven Seas due to a fumble. He finished his streak by shattering the race record (and the world record on 2000m turf) at the 2023 Autumn Tenno-sho and dominating a very stacked 2023 Japan Cup. He was retired to stud afterwards, citing he would not have been ready in time for the Arima Kinen.

He is Kitasan Black's first G1-winning progeny and proved himself to be not only one of the best racehorses of his generation but also becoming the best rated racehorse in the world. His victory at the 2023 Japan Cup made him Japan's greatest earning racehorse and, had he continued, he would have been well on his way to become Japan's first 7 G1 winner on turf with [b]no[/b] classic race wins.

In the context of [[Umamusume]], as the son of [[Kitasan Black (umamusume)|]], most fan designs portray him in some form of [[japanese clothes|Japanese-style outfit]], often with a Sun & Moon motif with a red and blue color scheme that references the [[racing colors]] of Silk Racing, Equinox's owner. He is also depicted together with [[King Halo (umamusume)|]] and/or [[Sakura Bakushin O (umamusume)|]] on some occasions.

h4. See also

* [[Christophe Lemaire]] - Equinox's [[jockey]]

title: nanase_yukika
body:
A character in [[Magia Record: Mahou Shoujo Madoka Magica Gaiden]].

h4. Appearance

Her [[blonde hair|blonde]] [[very long hair]] is tied into a [[low ponytail|low]] [[ponytail]] and decorated with a [[red hairband|red]] [[hairband]] and a [[red bow|red]] [[hair bow|bow]]. She also has [[crossed bangs]] [[hair between eyes|between her eyes]] and [[red eyes]].

In her daily life, she wears the [[Mizuna Girls' Academy school uniform]] paired with [[purple thighhighs|purple]] [[thighhighs]] with a [[single stripe]].

As a [[Magical Girl]], she wears [[fake animal ears|fake]] [[rabbit ears]], a [[red collar|red]] [[animal collar]] with a [[chain]] and a [[red gemstone|red]] [[heart|heart-shaped]] [[heart-shaped gem|gem]], a [[white shirt|white]] [[shirt]] with [[puffy short sleeves]] and [[breast pocket]]s, a pair of [[wrist cuffs]] and [[white gloves|white]] [[gloves]], a [[grey coat|grey]] [[sleeveless coat|sleeveless]] [[tailcoat]] with [[lapels]], a [[black corset|black]] [[corset]], a [[black skirt|black]] [[pencil skirt|pencil]] [[miniskirt]], [[red thighhighs|red]] [[argyle thighhighs|argyle]] [[thighhighs under boots|thighhighs]] with [[garter straps]] and [[red footwear|red]] [[ankle boots|ankle]] [[high heel boots|high heel]] [[boots]]. She fights using a [[rapier]].

* !asset #23411284
* !asset #23411285: [[Magical girl]]

Her [[Doppel (madoka magica)|]] form is [[Poker Alice]].

She is voiced by Sumi Tomomi Jiena, and was designed by [[Masu Gitsune]]/[[Kawazukuu]] duo.

This tag refers to the case in which these or other such identifying tags are worn through a [[nipple piercing]].

[[Keroro Gunsou]] character, and one of the protagonists. She has [[pink hair]], styled into [[twintails]] by default.

Outside of her [[Kissho Academy school uniform]], her standard outfit includes an [[orange jacket|orange]] [[short-sleeved jacket]] worn over [[short over long sleeves|long sleeves]].

h4. Trivia

title: houjou_mutsumi
body:
[[Keroro Gunsou]] character; called Saburo Mutsumi in the anime adaption. 

He has [[short hair|short]] [[grey hair]] and [[blue eyes]]. He is usually depicted in the [[Kissho Academy school uniform]], and often wears a [[yellow hat|yellow]] [[beanie]].

h4. Official art
* !asset #23404573

h4. Trivia
* "Mutsumi" can be read as "623". He uses this string of numbers as his moniker for the radio show he hosts and DJs.
* In the manga, this alias is "326".
* He is often seen with [[Kururu (keroro gunsou)|]], the only character to know his secret DJ identity.
* He is voiced by [[Ishida Akira]].


h4. See also
* [[List of Keroro Gunsou characters]]

title: angol_mois
body:
[[Keroro Gunsou]] character. She has [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair]] and [[orange eyes|orange]] or [[brown eyes]].

Her normal outfit consists of the [[summer uniform|Summer]] [[Kissho Academy school uniform]], and includes a [[yellow sweater vest]] over a [[white shirt|white]], [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] shirt, along with a [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[grey skirt]]. She also wears [[white leg warmers]] and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[shoes]].

h4. Official art
* !asset #23404208

h4. Trivia
* She is <spoiler>actually an Angol, a humanoid species known to destroy planets. Her alternate form is [[Angol Mois (Angol Form)]]</spoiler>.
* Her name derives from <spoiler>"Angolmois" - a term from the prophecies of Nostradamus. This is when he speaks about the reign of the "great king" of Angolmois, which is interpreted as being an anagram of the Old French word Mongolais, meaning 'Mongolians', and thus referring to Genghis Khan.</spoiler>


h4. See also
* [[List of Keroro Gunsou characters]]

title: mikeneko_(vtuber)
body:
A Japanese streamer. An [[indie utaite|independent]] [[utaite]] active from 2011 to 2017, came back in 2022 as an [[indie virtual youtuber|independent]] [[virtual YouTuber]].

On 24 April 2022, she officially debuted as a virtual YouTuber.

She joined [[VOICE-ORE]] in July 2023 under the alias Koito Ria until the group was disbanded on June 30, 2024.

She was supposed to debut as a musical artist under [[Pony Canyon]] in 2024 but those plans were cancelled on April 30, 2024.

h4. Versions

title: gundam_wing
body:
Popular animated [[Gundam]] series from the 90s. Began airing in 1995 and features a group of several young protagonists who operate different types of Gundam [[Mobile Suit]]s.

Extremely popular in the West during the year 2000, where it was broadcast in the [[Toonami]] block of [[Cartoon Network]] and had many action figures released as well in several popular toy stores in the USA, a first for a Gundam show.

title: gunpod
body:
A [b]gunpod[/b] is a detachable pod or pack containing [[machine gun]]s or an automatic [[cannon]], mounted externally on a vehicle. They are usually used in [[military]] [[aircraft]].

Gunpods increase an air combat vehicle's firepower without occupying internal volume. When not required for a specific mission they can be omitted to save weight so the vehicle becomes lighter, faster and consumes less fuel.

Also used in some anime [[science fiction]] [[mecha]] series like [[MACROSS]].

title: princess_celestia
body:
Princess Celestia is a secondary character in [[My Little Pony: Friendship Is Magic]].

She controls the day and sun, mentors [[Twilight Sparkle]], and is ruler of Equestria along with her sister, [[Princess Luna]]. 

Several alternate personalities for her have been created by fan works. She may be depicted as an overbearing tyrant who banishes any threat to the moon, a glorious bastard of a prankster known as Trollestia, or an unstoppable nymphomaniac known as Molestia.

* [b]English CV:[/b] Nicole Oliver
* [b]Japanese CV:[/b] [[Inoue Kikuko]] (seasons 1-2), Makuta Yuri (seasons 3-6)

title: frieren
body:
The titular protagonist of [[Sousou no Frieren]].

She is the Mage of the Hero Party and traveled alongside [[himmel (sousou no frieren)|Hero Himmel]], [[eisen (sousou no frieren)|Warrior Eisen]], and [[heiter|Priest Heiter]] in a ten-year journey to defeat the Demon King.

Several years later, she took on another journey with [[Stark (sousou no frieren)|Warrior Stark]] and her new disciple [[fern (sousou no frieren)|Mage Fern]], eventually reunited with her now elderly former party members. She is often known as "Frieren the Undertaker" (the title of the series).

Frieren is a [[petite]] female [[elf]] with [[green eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[white hair]] tied into [[twintails]] with [[parted bangs]]. Like all Elves, she has [[long pointy ears|large]], [[pointy ears]].

She wears a [[striped shirt|striped]] [[black shirt|black]] and [[white shirt]], along with a [[white jacket]] with [[gold trim|gold embellishments]] tucked into a [[skirt set|matching]] [[white skirt]] with a [[black belt]]. Over her jacket, she wears a gold-trimmed [[white capelet]] with a [[red gemstone]] on her [[high collar]]. She also wears [[black pantyhose]] and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[boots]], and a pair of [[gold earrings|gold]] and red [[earrings]] on each ear. She also carries a [[mage staff]].

[[aged down|In the past]], she had her [[hair down]] and wore a simple [[white dress]].

In the anime, she's voiced by [[Tanezaki Atsumi]] in Japanese and Mallorie Rodak in English.

h4. Official art

* !post #7397153: [[Frieren|Default]]
* !post #7397159: [[Frieren|Default (Reference)]]

* [[Frieren lap pillow (meme)]]

title: chain-link_fence
body:
A type of woven [[fence]] usually made from galvanized or LLDPE-coated steel [[wire]]. The wire runs vertically and is bent into a zig-zag pattern so each "zig" is quickly trapped on one side with the wire and each "zag" with the wire quickly traps the other. This forms the characteristic [[diamond (shape)|]] pattern seen on this type of fence.

h4. See also

* [[bamboo fence]]
* [[iron fence]]
* [[wooden fence]]
** [[picket fence]]

title: zalgo_commentary
body:
Zalgo is a form of text formatting associated with [[creepypasta]], [[demon|demons]], and [[eldritch abomination|eldritch abominations]].  It uses various tricks, particularly Unicode "combining diacritics":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combining_Diacritical_Marks and control characters that change the text flow direction. The result is text that appears corrupted, glitchy and partially overwritten by eldritch symbols.

Zalgo text originated in fan edits of the comic strip [[Garfield]], usually containing the phrase "He Comes!".

h1. External Links
https://zalgo.org: A text generator used to summon H̶̘̚̚I̵̲̱͗̓M̴͍͈͌

body:
Collective name for anonymous artists on Western imageboards, such as those found in [[4chan]]'s long combo of threads since summer 2010.

Do not use this tag if an artist's identity is known or if art comes from pixiv. If the artist is known, use the appropriate artist tag rather than this one.

title: isuzu_ren
body:
A character in [[Magia Record: Mahou Shoujo Madoka Magica Gaiden]].

h4. Appearance

She has [[blue eyes]] and [[grey hair|grey]] [[medium hair]] with [[long bangs|long]] [[diagonal bangs]] that [[one eye covered|cover]] [[hair over one eye|one eye]].

In her daily life, she wears the [[Kamihama University Affiliated School uniform]] paired with [[black thighhighs|black]] [[thighhighs]].

As a [[Magical Girl]], she wears a [[white flower|white]] [[hair flower|flower]], a [[blue ribbon|blue]] [[tress ribbon|tress]] [[hair ribbon|ribbon]], a [[blue choker|blue]] [[choker]], a [[blue gemstone|blue]] [[chest jewel]], a [[short kimono|short]] [[white kimono|white]]  (or with a pair of [[shoulder cutout]]s) [[right-over-left kimono|right-over-left]] [[kimono]] worn [[off shoulder|hanging off her arms]] with [[long sleeves|long]] [[wide sleeves]] and its [[hooded kimono|hood]] [[hood down|down]], a [[short dress|short]] [[black dress|black]] [[dress]]/[[black shirt|black]] [[sleeveless shirt|shirt]] with [[spaghetti strap|spaghetti]] [[sleeveless dress|straps]], a [[white bow|white]] [[waist bow]], a [[thigh strap]], [[single thighhigh|single]] [[black thighhighs|black]] [[thighhighs|thighhigh]], and [[white footwear|white]] [[ankle boots|ankle]] [[boots]]. She fights with a [[staff]].

She may occasionally be portrayed with [[white wings|white]] [[feathered wings|feathered]] [[angel wings|wi]][[wings|ngs]].

title: eous_(zenless_zone_zero)
body:
The [[Bangboo (Zenless Zone Zero)|]] in [[Zenless Zone Zero]] operated by Phaethon ([[Wise (Zenless Zone Zero)|]] and [[Belle (Zenless Zone Zero)|]]). It is used to guide the Hollow Raiders through the Hollows, thus it is the most likely to be out and about.

It wears an [[orange bandana|orange]] [[bandana]] around its neck with the number "01" printed on it.

Belle and Wise own at least two other Bangboo identical in appearance to Eous except for the number on the bandana: [[Bangboo 18 (zenless zone zero)|]] and [[Bangboo 6 (zenless zone zero)|]]. However, since Eous is the one most commonly seen, if the number isn't visible or not drawn at all, it's fine to use this tag.

When using this tag, please also tag [[Tamagotchi]], and if possible, the model portrayed (such as [[tamagotchi (classic)|Classic]] or [[tamagotchi connection|Connection]]).

title: eri_aimi
body:
A character in [[Magia Record: Mahou Shoujo Madoka Magica Gaiden]]. 

h4. Appearance

Her [[medium hair|medium-length]] [[wavy hair|wavy]] [[orange hair]] is tied into [[low twintails|low]] [[twintails]] or let out loose. She also has [[sidelocks]], [[swept bangs]] and [[orange eyes]].

In her daily life, she wears the [[Chuo Academy school uniform]] paired with [[white thighhighs]] and a [[ring]]. 

As a [[Magical Girl]], she wears a [[brown headwear|brown]] [[cowboy hat|cowboy]] [[hat]], a [[frilled jacket|frilled]] [[orange jacket|orange]] [[jacket]] with [[long sleeves]], [[lapels]] and [[buttons]], a [[purple dress|purple]]-and-[[brown dress|brown]] [[dress]] with [[frilled dress|frills]], an [[orange gemstone|orange]] [[gem]], a [[black belt|black]] [[belt]], [[grey thighhighs|grey]] [[vertical-striped thighhighs|vertical-striped]] [[thighhighs]] ([[zettai ryouiki]]) and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[fold-over boots|fold-over]] [[cross-laced footwear|cross-]][[lace-up boots|laced]] [[high heel boots|heel]] [[boots]]. She fights with a [[gun]]. 

* !asset #23404827
* !asset #23404826: [[Magical girl]]
* !asset #23404829: [[eri aimi (winter costume)|Winter costume]]

She is voiced by [[Ueda Reina]].

h4. External links

* "Puella Magica Wiki: Aimi Eri":https://wiki.puella-magi.net/Aimi_Eri

title: awane_kokoro
body:
A character in [[Magia Record: Mahou Shoujo Madoka Magica Gaiden]].

h4. Appearance

Her [[brown hair]] is typically tied into [[hair rings|rings]], leaving out a [[single sidelock|single]] [[low-tied sidelocks|low-tied sidelock]], and decorated with [[cube hair ornaments|cubes]]. She also has [[blunt bangs|blunt]] [[diagonal bangs|diagonal]] [[bangs]] and [[green eyes]].

In her daily life, she wears [[Chuo Academy school uniform]] paired with [[white thighhighs|white]] [[thighhighs]].

As a [[Magical Girl]], she wears a [[yellow headwear|yellow]] [[hat]], a [[black bodysuit|black]] or [[grey bodysuit|grey]] [[sleeveless bodysuit|sleeveless]] with a [[collared bodysuit|collar]], a [[white ascot|white]] [[ascot]] with a [[green gemstone|green]] [[brooch]], a [[yellow shirt|yellow]] [[off-shoulder shirt|off-shoulder]] [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] [[crop top|crop]] [[shirt|top]] with a [[zipper]], [[yellow gloves|yellow]] [[gloves]], am [[orange skirt|orange]] [[showgirl skirt]] with a [[red gemstone]] and [[yellow footwear|yellow]] [[boots]].

* !asset #23404715

A [[Virtual YouTuber]] associated with [[MyHolo TV]]. She is a part of MonstarZ alongside [[Athelia Hiroyuki]] and [[Virion Kisei]].

* Facebook "Lunaris Urufi":[https://www.facebook.com/lunarisurufi]

A smiley that is used to represent a face with squinted eyes (mouth shape is often varied).

It is primarily used to express contentment but can occasionally be used for anything from exasperation to embarrassment or sleepiness.

h4. See also

* [[Tag Group:Eyes tags]]

title: nanashi_inc.

title: 7up
body:
7 Up, stylized as [b]7up[/b], is a brand of lemon-lime flavored [[soda]].

In the US the brand had the mascot character [[Cool Spot]], who was the main character of the 1993 console game of the same name.

The character [[Fido Dido]] is used as 7up's mascot world-wide, except in the US where PepsiCo does not make 7up.

title: fido_dido
body:
[b]Fido Dido[/b] is a cartoon character of a male youth created by Joanna Ferrone and Sue Rose.

The character has been licensed by [[Pepsi|PepsiCo]] and used as a mascot for various products, such as [[7up]] and Slice.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Fido Dido":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fido_Dido]

title: raiden_mei_(danzai_spectramancer)
body:
A playable [[official alternate costume|battlesuit]] of [[Honkai Impact 3rd]]'s [[Raiden Mei]]. 

In her base Danzai Spectramancer form, she is portrayed wearing a [[black dress|black]] and [[red dress|red]] [[layered dress]] with [[red armor]]ed pieces, and is an augmented form of [[raiden mei (shadow dash)|Shadow Dash]]. 

She has one [[official alternate costume]] with this outfit, the more popular [[raiden mei (orochi cuirass)|Orochi Cuirass]] version. 

h4. Appearance

* !post #4639868: Left side (Orochi Cuirass version)

title: bronya_zaychik_(herrscher_of_reason)
body:
One of the playable [[official alternate costume|battlesuits]] of [[Honkai Impact 3rd]]'s [[Bronya Zaychik]]. 

The base Herrscher of Reason battlesuit consists of a [[frilled dress|frilled]] [[two-tone dress|two-tone]] [[layered dress]] ([[black dress|black]] upper and [[white dress|white]] lower) with a [[navel cutout]], [[black gloves|black]] [[elbow gloves]] with [[blue gloves|blue hands]], orange [[earrings]], [[white footwear|white]] [[thigh boots]], and a black-blue [[butterfly hair ornament]] on the left side of her head. 

She has one other alternate costume with this outfit: her [[bronya_zaychik_(magic_girl_bronya)|mahou shoujo]] dress. 

h4. Appearance

* !post #5375656: Default
* !post #4892754: [[bronya_zaychik_(magic_girl_bronya)|Magic Girl Bronya]]

title: joker_(dc)
body:
[[Batman|Batman's]] archnemesis and the main antagonist of [[DC comics]]' [i][[batman (series)|Batman]][/i] series and movies. A maniacal clown with green hair, bleached skin and a grotesque grin, Joker is a brilliant criminal mastermind and expert chemist who specializes in weaponized props and toxins. He is also a murderous psychopath with a horrific sense of humor and a pathological obsession with Batman.

The Joker is created by the late Bob Kane, the late Bill Finger, and the late Jerry Robinson and first appeared in [i]Batman[/i] #1 (April 25, 1940).

h4. Notable Incarnations
* The Joker ([[Batman: the Animated Series]]) - The Joker as portrayed in the DC Animated Universe
* [[Arthur Fleck]] - Civilian identity in the [i][[joker (2019)|JOKER]][/i] continuity
* [[Jerome Valeska]] and [[Jeremiah Valeska]] - Civilian identities in the [i][[Gotham (series)]][/i] continuity

title: marisa_(street_fighter)
body:
Her full name is [b]Marisa Rosetti[/b]. She is a character from [[Street Fighter]], first debuting in [[Street Fighter 6]]. She is currently the tallest and heaviest female fighter in the game, owning to her extremely [[muscular female|muscular]] build.

A [[Greece|Greco]]-[[Italy|Italian]] jewelry designer and pankration wrestler. Despite her intimidating stature and her use of aggresive fighting technique, Marisa is an upbeat and well-mannered fighter who seeks thrill of combat and living her life to its fullest.

She is notable for being the first [[bisexual female|bisexual]] and polyamourous character of the Street Fighter franchise, proclaiming that she "has enough love for everyone".

h5. Official Bio

An up-and-coming jewelry designer from Italy who claims ancestry to ancient Greek warriors. As a child, she was inspired by a vision of the Colosseum in its prime. Today, she seeks glory with a smile—and an eye for beauty.

* [b]Hates:[/b] Heights
* [b]Likes:[/b] Worthy opponents, ossobuco, fine arts
* [b]Height:[/b] 203cm / 6'8"
* [b]Weight:[/b] 122kg / 269 lbs
other_names: マリーザ(ストリートファイター)

title: dib_(invader_zim)
body: Character from [[Invader Zim]], a 12-year-old (as of Enter the Florpus) self-styled "paranormal investigator", and one of only two people on Earth (the other being his sister Gaz) to realize Zim's extraterrestrial origin. Dib's goal is to expose paranormal phenomena to the rest of the world, especially his father. However he is regarded as a loon by pretty much everyone, and essentially treated like crap by the very people whose lives he's trying to save. Nonetheless, while he means well, he's fairly ruthless (at times bordering on sadistic) when it comes to dealing with Zim, making them Mirror Characters to each other.

title: astonaige_medoz
body:
A fictional character from the [[Gundam]] series. He first appeared in the [[Zeta Gundam]] TV anime series from 1985. Also appears in the sequel TV series [[Gundam ZZ]] (1986) and the anime film [[Char's Counterattack]] (1988).

[b]Astoinage Medoz[/b] is the chief [[Mobile Suit]] mechanic of the AEUG [[Argama]] and [[Nahel Argama]]  [[military]] [[spacecraft]]. He later becomes part of the [[earth_federation_space_forces|Londo Bell fleet]] and the chief MS mechanic in the [[Ra Cailum]] spacecraft, where he starts a relationship with MS pilot [[Kayra Su]]. [spoiler]He died during the final battle of the Second [[Neo Zeon]] War when a stray [[Geara Doga]] [[beam rifle]] shot hit him while attending MS units at the ship's launch pad.[/spoiler]

The effect of treating an image as multi-layered paper, where ripping or removing one or more layers reveals something else (e.g. a successively less-dressed version of the character in the same pose, or the [[circuit board]] inside an electronic device).

The Pixiv tag is 妄撮 ([i]Mousatsu[/i]), pin-ups of an extinct [[magazine (object)|]] called [i]KING[/i]. Later, this effect was featured in some photo books and these books made a big hit.

title: ph1lza
body:
[[Minecraft YouTube]]r who has played for many years, best known for his two 5 year old Hardcore worlds and his characters on [[Dream SMP]] and [[Quackity SMP]].

His persona is a man with [[medium hair|medium length]] [[blonde hair]] and [[blue eyes]] who wears a green and white striped [[bucket hat]] and [[green kimono]]. He is often given black [[bird wings]] based on a crow's.

His persona is modeled after [[Urahara Kisuke]], though artists often [[adapted costume|deviate from the original design]].

Both he and [[Technoblade]] are frequently drawn with matching [[crystal earrings|emerald earrings]], a reference to the Dream SMP, where the two have matching "friendship emeralds". He is also frequently depicted with a [[hardcore heart]] emblem somewhere.

title: magma_taishi_(character)
body:
A character and protagonist from the [[Magma Taishi]] science fiction [[super robot]] manga and [[tokusatsu]] series from the 60s.

[b]Magma[/b] (マグマ [i]Maguma[/i]) is a [[giant]] humanoid [[alien]] [[mecha]] hero forged in [[gold]] who just like his human-sized wife [[Mol (magma taishi)|]] and son [[Gam (magma taishi)|]], transforms into a giant [[rocket]]. He has long human-like [[blonde hair]] and also fires [[missile]]s out of a panel located in his chest, and shoots electrical bolts from his [[antennae]].

Magma is considered one of the earliest [[Transformers]], even before the anime super robot, [[Yuusha Raideen]], set the standard for the genre.

According to character creator [[Tezuka Osamu]], Magma is technically not a true [[super robot]], but an [[alien]] [[giant]] made of gold. However, because of his appearance and powers he has been classified as such since decades ago.

title: hopeless_masquerade
body:
A [[Touhou]] fighting game, officially designated as "Touhou 13.5" (as its events take place between [i][[Ten Desires]][/i] and [i][[Double Dealing Character]][/i]).  A demo with three playable characters was released 30 December 2012 at [[Comiket]] 83; the full version followed 26 May 2013 during [[Reitaisai]] 10 (alongside the demo for [i]Double Dealing Character[/i]).

The storyline centers on representatives of the three major faiths in [[Gensokyo]] -- Shinto, Buddhism, and Taoism -- battling it out in the wake of an overall crisis of faith in the Human Village.  

h4. Playable Characters

* [[Hakurei Reimu]] (also in demo)

title: toonami
body:
A programming block on the [[Cartoon Network]]/[[Adult Swim]] channel, geared towards airing action animation, generally manifesting itself in more action-oriented Western cartoons and, famously, anime. It originally ran from 1997 to 2008 on Cartoon Network, before a 2012 Adult Swim Toonami-themed April Fools would lead to the block being revived that same year, and running on Adult Swim ever since.

The block was originally hosted by the [[Space Ghost (series)|Space Ghost Coast to Coast]] incarnation of Moltar, before the [[Toonami Operations Module]], or TOM, debuted in 1999 to take over hosting responsibilities. TOM has switched bodies several times since his debut.

On Cartoon Network Japan, Toonami existed as a block from 2002 (during TOM 2's run) up to 2008 when it was cancelled around the same time as the US original was. TOM was subtitled in his appearances there. In 2018, for Adult Swim's April Fools, Toonami would partially air in Japanese, with TOM being voiced by Masa Kanome.

title: finding_nemo
body:
Finding Nemo is a 2003 American animated comedy-drama adventure film produced by [[pixar|Pixar Animation Studios]] for Walt Disney Pictures.
It tells the story of an overprotective clownfish named Marlin who, along with a forgetful regal blue tang named Dory, searches for his missing son Nemo. Along the way, Marlin learns to take risks and comes to terms with Nemo taking care of himself.

title: ricardo_brust
body:
Ricardo Salas Brust, better known as Ricardo Brust (born March 26, 1967) is a [[mexico|Mexican]] voice actor and announcer. He also studied Computer Systems Engineering.

He is mainly recognized for having dubbed characters such as [[cell (dragon_ball)|Cell]], [[Broly (dragon_ball_z)|Broly]] and [[Mr. Satan]] in the [[Dragon Ball]] franchise, Owl in the [[Winnie The Pooh]] franchise, Denarian Rhomann Dey in [[Guardians of the Galaxy]], Crush in [[Finding Nemo]] and [[Finding Dory]], the Abominable Snowman in the [[Monsters Inc.]] franchise, among many others.

title: mr._satan
body:
A character from [[Dragon Ball Z]]. Also known as [b]Hercule Satan[/b] in the Funimation dub, he's the World Martial Arts Champion and the (self-proclaimed) protector of Earth. Father of [[Videl]]. His real name is [b]Mark[/b]. 

Initially introduced as a boastful, loud-mouthed comic relief. Although Satan is very strong for a human, he is no match for the various super fighters within the series, with him ending up running away from any threats and being viewed as a coward by those around him. He does, however, posses a strong sense of justice and luck, as Satan occasionally using his worldwide fame among ordinary earthlings to aid the protagonists in the fight. <spoilers>Most notably convincing the earthlings to spare their spirit energy to create the [[genki dama]] during [[Son Goku]]'s final fight against [[Kid Buu]] by using his name.</spoilers>

Voiced by [[Gouri Daisuke]] (1993-2010) and [[Ishizuka Unshou]] (2010-2018). Voiced by [[Ricardo Brust]] in the latin american dub.

At school, he wears the standard [[yumenosaki school uniform|Yumenosaki uniform]], consisting on [[plaid pants]], and a [[blue jacket|blue]] [[blazer]] with a [[yellow sweater]] [[sweater under jacket|beneath it]].

title: bitter_glasse_(umamusume)
body:
[[Umamusume]] game-only character. Member of Team First under Acting Chairwoman [[Kashimoto Riko]].

[[Horse girl]]. Has [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair|brown]] hair and [[brown eyes]]. She has [[dark skin]] and she also wears an ornament and ribbon around [b]her right ear[/b].

Like [[Happy Meek (umamusume)|]], Bitter Glasse is an "original umagirl", i.e. not based on any particular real-life horse. However, as it is often the case with popular pop culture, there's a real-life horse named [i]after[/i] her.

Bitter Glace (note the different spelling) is a bay [b]filly[/b] (not a colt as one would expect from the ear decoration placement) sired by Rulership and foaled by Anthology. Rulership is a son of [[King Kamehameha (umamusume)|]] and [[Air Groove (umamusume)|]] while Anthology is a daughter of [[Sakura Bakushin O (umamusume)|]] and Pops (herself a daughter of [[Sunday Silence (racehorse)|]]).

As an apparent nod to her, Bitter Glasse is said to go to the Miho dormitory according to dorm head [[Hishi Amazon (umamusume)|]].

h5. External links

* "Umamusume Official Character Bio: Bitter Glasse":[https://umamusume.jp/character/bitterglasse]
other_names: ビターグラッセ(ウマ娘)

title: happy_meek_(umamusume)
body:
Character from [i][[Umamusume]][/i].

[[Kiryuuin Aoi]]'s charge. Happy Meek isn't based on any particular racehorse but she seems to be the only genuine white horse of the franchise (dominant white is an extremely uncommon color for throughbreds - very few thrived in the racetrack and only one horse ([[Sodashi (racehorse)|]]) has ever won a G1 race - all the other white-haired horse girls were actually based on gray horses). That being said, she is likely modeled either on Hakutaiyu, Japan's first white horse or on Shirayukihime's several descendants (like Sodashi herself).

Happy Meek is a [[horse girl]] with [[short_hair|short]] [[white hair]] (usually portrayed as an off-white), [[pink eyes]] with a flower hairclip over her left temple and an ornament made out of small flowers around [b]her right ear[/b] (although, in her case, this might be irrelevant).

h5. External links

* "Umamusume Official Character Bio: Happy Meek":[https://umamusume.jp/character/happymeek]

[[Horse girl]]. Has [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair|blonde]] hair (with a single [[blue hair|blue]] [[streaked hair|highlight]]) and [[green eyes]]. She also wears a [[purple bow|purple]] [[hair bow]] positioned in front and to the right of [b]her right ear[/b].

Like [[Happy Meek (umamusume)|]], Little Cocon is an "original umagirl", i.e. not based on any particular real-life horse. However, as it is often the case with popular pop culture, there's a real-life horse named [i]after[/i] her.

This chestnut colt is a son of Big Arthur and foaled by Break Dancer. He is a sire-line grandson of [[Sakura Bakushin O (umamusume)|]] and, on the mother's side, a descendant of [[Sunday Silence (racehorse)|]] through Dance in the Dark.

title: otaku
body:
A person obsessed with any subject, whether anime, manga, [[comic]]s, entertainment, [[video game]]s, electronics, [[toy]]s, trains, vehicles, weapons, [[history]], etc.

The term started as a derogatory term in [[Japan]] during the late 70s towards anti-social people who are highly fixated over a particular subject or person, but has since evolved (in the West mostly) to imply a cool, eccentric individual with particularly unique hobbies or interests. However, depictions of generic otaku as an "unhealthily obsessive fan" stock character remains in widespread uses in media (specially in Japan). In the West, otaku are often conflated with Western nerds, to the point of the term being used as a synonym, but each have their own specific differences socially and culturally. For the purposes of Danbooru though, they are one and the same. 

Tag what you see: The tag is only applicable if the image shows their otakuness/nerdiness.

title: idol
body:
In the Japanese context, idols are generally young entertainers with a combination of [[singing]] and [[dancing]], who usually wear [[idol clothes|very showy or frilly outfits]]. 

Several game, manga and anime series include idols or are even centered around idols, including [[Idolmaster]], [[Love Live!]], [[Aikatsu!]], [[Pretty series|the Pretty series]], [[Uta no Prince-sama]], [[Macross]], and [[Mahou no Tenshi Creamy Mami]], the latter two being generally considered the start of idols in anime.

Fans dedicated to a single idol are participating in [[oshi-katsu]].

Latin: [i]Strigops habroptilus[/i]

title: lobotomy_corporation_(identity)_(project_moon)
body:
[[list of project moon Identities|Identities]] of [[Limbus Company]] Sinners extracted from mirror worlds where they joined the [[Lobotomy Corporation]] as [[employee (project moon)|employees]] during the events of that game. They are exclusive to the Walpurgisnacht banners and can only be obtained through extraction/the dispenser during those times.

Each one has the title of Lobotomy E.G.O and use the [[E.G.O_(project moon)|E.G.O equipment]] of an abnormality. The title is partially shared with [[Technology Liberation Alliance (identity) (project moon)|Technology Liberation Alliance identities]], but exclusively utilize E.G.O equipment first introduced in [[Lobotomy Corporation]].
* Faust's identity is based on a [[Malkuth (project moon)|Control Team]] employee using the [[regret_(e.g.o)|E.G.O equipment]] of [[Forsaken Murderer]].
* Don Quixote's identity is based on a [[Hod (project moon)|Training Team]] employee using the [[lantern_(e.g.o)|E.G.O equipment]] of [[Meat Lantern (project moon)|]]. However, she is also equipped with the E.G.O gifts from [[Void Dream]] and [[Fragment of the Universe]].
* Outis' identity is based on a [[Hod (project moon)|Training Team]] employee using the [[magic_bullet_(e.g.o)|E.G.O equipment]] of [[Der Freischuetz (project moon)|Der Freischütz]].
* Yi Sang's identity is based on a [[Netzach (project moon)|Safety Team]] employee using the [[solemn_lament_(e.g.o)|E.G.O equipment]] of [[Funeral of the Dead Butterflies]].
* Ryoshu's identity is based on both a [[Netzach (project moon)|Safety Team]] employee [spoiler]and the [[Gebura (project moon)|Red Mist]][/spoiler] [[asymmetrical dual wielding|dual wielding]] [[Red Eyes (e.g.o)|]] and [[Penitence (e.g.o)|]] from [[Spider Bud]] and [[One Sin and Hundreds of Good Deeds]] respectively. 

h3. Playable Identities:

title: wuthering_heights_(identity)_(project_moon)
body:
[[list of project moon Identities|Identities]] of [[Limbus Company]] Sinners extracted from Mirror Worlds where they joined a faction of, or were deeply connected to, the Wuthering Heights estate as visited in Canto VI.

The [b]Edgar Family[/b] is a faction consisting of the titular family and the [[butler|butlers]] who are under their employ. Male butlers wear a uniform consisting of a formal [[black suit]] over a [[white shirt]] and [[white ascot]]. Female butlers wear [[frills|frilled]] [[maid]] outfit complete with [[maid headdress]], with the head butler wearing a [[grey ascot]] instead of a [[grey ribbon|grey]] [[neck ribbon]]. The staff opt to use [[cutlery]] as weapons, particularly [[knife|knives]], while their master uses a [[rapier]].

The [b]Wuthering Heights Butlers[/b] are instead contracted to be loyal to the owner of the mansion itself. They dress as [[butler|butlers]] regardless of [[female butler|gender]] and wear a [[brown suit]] over a [[white shirt]] with two [[neck ribbon|neck ribbons]], one being a [[bow tie]]. They fight using [[martial arts]] and always hold [[towel|towels]] to minimize blood getting on their outfits.

* Faust's identity is based on a standard Wuthering Heights butler.
* Ryoshu's identity is based on [[Nelly (project moon)|]].
* Sinclair's identity is based on a standard Wuthering Heights butler.
* Heathcliff's identity is based on[spoilers], but not the same as, [[Erlking Heathcliff (project moon)|]][/spoilers].
* Ishmael's identity is based on a standard Linton Family butler.
* Outis' identity is based on [[Josephine (project moon)|]].
* Gregor's identity is based on [[Linton (project moon)|]].

h3. Playable Identities:

title: lobotomy_corporation_remnant_(identity)_(project_moon)
body:

Unlike the [[lobotomy corporation (identity) (project moon)|Lobotomy Corporation identities]], they were not in the specific facility that the game's events took place in and were instead left to be buried alive along with their branches following the aftermath. title: multicrack_office_(identity)_(project_moon)
body:
[[list of project moon Identities|Identities]] of [[Limbus Company]] Sinners extracted from mirror worlds where they joined MultiCrack Office, an office of Fixers that exclusively employ [[prosthesis]] [[cyborg|users]]. The Office first appears in the second Intervallo of Canto VI.

They originate from the cold North section of the City and wear [[red jacket|red jackets]] over [[white coat|white coats]] and [[black mask|black]] [[mouth mask|mouth masks]]. Standard-issue prosthetics for their Fixers include [[mechanical arms]]. High-ranking members tend to have [[extra arms|four arms]], often at least [[dual wielding]] and sometimes [[quadruple wielding]] in battle, with their weapons of choices being [[glaive (polearm)|glaives]] or [[zweihander|zweihanders]] to demonstrate how much stronger their arms are than human ones.

* Faust's identity is based off of Sasha.
* Heathcliff's identity is based off an unnamed MultiCrack Fixer the Sinners meet at the WARP train platform.

title: w_corp._(identity)_(project_moon)
body:
[[list of project moon Identities|Identities]] of [[Limbus Company]] Sinners extracted from mirror worlds where they joined WARP Corp, the Wing of the City in control of District 23, and the operators of the WARP Train network.

W. Corp Cleanup Agents are responsible for identifying and returning the biomass of passengers back to their seats before restoring their forms to what they were prior to the time-dilated travel aboard the vehicles. Their uniforms consist of [[black hat|black]] [[baseball cap|baseball caps]], a [[black vest]] over a [[blue necktie]] and [[blue shirt]], [[black gloves]], and [[black pants]]. They are equipped with several [[bag|bags]] strapped onto their arms and legs and use melee weapons that can be charged with energy. This energy also allows them to create [[portal_(object)|portals]] to jump through, and they are often depicting fighting [[train interior|aboard the trains]].

Their rankings are in descending order, with L3 being higher than L2.

* Outis' identity loosely references Rose as she appears in [[Library of Ruina]].
* All other identities are not based on specific characters and are instead based on generic cleanup agents.

They all wear [[chinese clothes|Chinese-inspired attire]], and the standard uniform consists of a [[black vest]] with a [[red necktie]] fastened with a gold [[tie clip]] and [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt]] underneath. title: edna_krabappel
body:
One of the many characters of the [[united_states|American]] animated comedy sitcom [[The Simpsons]], she was the teacher of [[Bart Simpson]].
Al Jean announced Edna would be retired due to the death of Marcia Wallace (her voice actress) on October 25, 2013. The process began in "Four Regrettings and a Funeral" when "We'll really miss you Mrs. K." was shown on the chalkboard gag during the title sequence, which premiered nine days after Marcia's death. In the Season 25 episode "The Man Who Grew Too Much", [[ned flanders|Ned]] and Nelson mentioned that they miss her. Her passing was indicated by Ned wearing a black armband, but was never shown on-screen.
other_names: エドナ・クラバーペル

title: sideshow_bob
body:
A villain in [[The Simpsons]], who has a real grudge against Bart.
He is voiced by Kelsey Grammer and first appeared in the episode "The Telltale Head". Bob is a self-proclaimed genius who is a graduate of Yale University and a champion of high culture, including the adoption of a transatlantic accent, similar to that of Grammer's portrayal of Dr. Frasier Crane from the sitcoms [[Cheers!]] and [[Frasier]].

title: sena_mikoto
body:
A character in [[Magia Record: Mahou Shoujo Madoka Magica Gaiden]]. She is the human form of the [[witch (madoka magica)|Mirror Witch]], which is also known as [[Winchester (madoka magica)|]]/Sarah Mirabilis W.

h4. Appearance

Her [[very long hair|very long]] [[light blue hair|light]] [[blue hair]] is typically tied into [[tri tails]], two of which also count as [[low-tied sidelocks|low-tied]] [[sidelocks]]. She also has an [[ahoge]] and [[purple eyes]].

In her daily life, she wears the [[Daitou Academy school uniform|Daitou Academy uniform]] paired with [[grey pantyhose|grey]] [[pantyhose]].

As a [[Magical Girl]], she wears [[white flower|white]] [[hair flower|flowers in her hair]], a [[white headwear|white]] [[bonnet]], a [[black collar|black]] [[detached collar]] with [[grey gemstone]]s, a [[grey shirt|grey]] [[shirt]], a [[white dress|white]] [[medium dress|medium]] [[sleeveless dress|sleeveless]] [[two-tone dress|-and-]][[black dress|black]] [[frilled dress]] (occasionally depicted as [[strapless dress|strapless]] instead) with a [[black bow|black]] [[back bow]] and [[cross-laced dress|cross-]][[cross-laced clothes|lacing]], [[long sleeves|long]] [[juliet sleeves|juliet]] [[detached sleeves]] with [[frilled sleeves|frills]] that appear to be [[layered sleeves|layered]], a [[black skirt|black]] [[overskirt]], [[grey pantyhose|grey]] [[pantyhose]], and [[blue footwear|blue]] [[glass slipper]]s. She fights using a [[hand mirror]].

* !asset #23388091: [[Uwasa no Mikoto]]

title: felix_dzerzhinsky
body:
Felix Edmundovich Dzerzhinsky (Феликс Эдмундович Дзержинский) was a Polish-born Soviet revolutionary and politician who served as the leader of two early Soviet secret police organisations, the Cheka and the OGPU. Under his leadership, tens to hundreds of thousands of dissidents were killed during the [Red Terror](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_Terror) campaign. Several monuments were made of Dzerzhinsky, one of which was located in Lubyanka Square. It was famously [dismantled](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monument_to_Felix_Dzerzhinsky,_Moscow#August_coup_and_Muzeon_Park_relocation) after the failed [1991 coup attempt](https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=1991_Soviet_coup_d%27%C3%A9tat_attempt).

h4. External Links
* [Wikipedia: Felix Dzerzhinsky](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Felix_Dzerzhinsky)

title: cdawgva
body:
Connor Marc Colquhoun, also known online as [b]CDawgVA[/b], is a Welsh YouTuber and voice actor who currently works in Japan.

He, along with fellow YouTubers Joey Bizinger ([[The Anime Man]]) and Garnt Maneetapho ([[Gigguk]]) are the hosts of the weekly podcast show, [[Trash Taste]].

Is also a frequent collaborator with [[virtual youtuber]] [[Ironmouse]], where fans have jokingly called them husband and wife due to their constant bickering.

title: super_crown
body:
A powerup in [[New Super Mario Bros. U Deluxe]] that transforms [[Toadette]] into [[Peachette]], a [[Princess Peach]] lookalike retaining some original form attributes, with Peach's abilities and more. Canonically, the game's official website states only she can use it.

Fans, however, used it to similarly transform [[Bowser]], and from there on [[King Boo]], then many more characters, and even [[personification|personify]] items, from the [[mario (series)|Mario universe]]. More specifically in human female, but no additional abilities. The more esoteric the subject, the less “lookalike” or even “human” applies.

The trend is known as “peachifying” (ピーチ姫化) in Japan. The result is typically named with either an "-ette" suffix (in reference to Peachette), or by default a “princess” title like Peach ("-Hime" suffix in Japanese).

h4. Tagging rules
According to topic #15603, peachifying is its own distinct change and resulting character:
* Don't tag the regular form character or [[Princess Peach]]. (post #3262233).
* Don't tag [[cosplay]]. (post #3262904)
* Tag [[transformation]] only if the change is shown or suggested. (post #3262233).
* Tag [[genderswap]] only if the change is shown or suggested, or the expected result is swapped. (post #3265315)
* Copyright tag with [[New Super Mario Bros. U Deluxe]], not the origin of the character's regular form.
…unless otherwise also present caveat for all these rules.

title: tokime_shizuka
body:
A character in [[Magia Record: Mahou Shoujo Madoka Magica Gaiden]].

h4. Appearance

She has [[purple eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[grey hair]] with [[sidelocks]]; usually tied into [[twintails]].

In her daily life, she wears a [[red headwear|red]] [[beret]] with a [[striped bow|striped]] [[hat bow|bo]][[bow|w]], a [[brown bowtie|brown]]/[[purple bowtie|purple]] [[bowtie]], a shirt with a pair of [[long sleeves|long]] [[white sleeves]] with [[sleeve cuffs|cuffs]]; a [[ring]], a [[skirt set]] consisting of a [[red vest|red]] [[pinstripe vest|pinstripe]] [[vest]] with [[buttons]] and a [[wing collar]]; a [[red skirt|red]] [[pinstripe skirt|pinstripe]] [[medium skirt|medium]] [[skirt]] with [[frilled skirt|frills]] and a [[brown bow|brown]]/[[purple bow|purple]] [[back bow]]; [[black pantyhose]] and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[loafers]].

As a [[Magical Girl]], she wears [[purple ribbon|purple]] and [[yellow ribbon|yellow]] [[hair ribbon|ribbons]], a [[brown scarf|brown]]/[[purple scarf|purple]] [[scarf]], a [[short kimono|short]] [[purple kimono|purple]] [[kimono]] with [[short sleeves]], a [[kimono skirt]] and [[frilled kimono|frills]]; a [[yellow sash|yellow]] [[obi]] with a [[back bow]], [[wide sleeves|wide]] [[detached sleeves|detached]] [[furisode]] sleeves, [[bridal gauntlets]], [[white thighhighs|white]] [[thighhighs|thighhigh]] [[tabi]], and [[okobo]]. She fights with a [[seven-branched sword]].

title: angel_day
body:
Angel Day is a [[date pun]] that occurs on October 4th. Use this tag for Angel related artworks posted on 10/04.

October is the 10th month, pronounced "ten" in English. 4 is pronounced よん("yon") or し("shi") in Japanese. So 10/04 sounds like "Tenshi" (天使), which means angel in japanese.

title: aoba_chika
body:
A character in [[Magia Record: Mahou Shoujo Madoka Magica Gaiden]].

h4. Appearance

Her [[very long hair|very long]] [[white hair]] is [[parted hair|parted in the middle]], tied into [[low-tied long hair|low]] [[low twintails|twintails]] and decorated with [[white flower|white]] [[hair flower|flowers]]. She also has her [[hair between eyes|bangs between eyes]] and [[blue eyes]].

In her daily life, she wears the [[st._liliana's_academy_school_uniform|Saint Liliana's Academy uniform]] paired with [[white socks|white]] [[socks]].

As a [[Magical Girl]], her hair assumes a [[light blue hair|light blue]] tint, and has an [[ahoge]]. She wears a [[head wreath|flower crown]], [[earrings]], a [[striped scarf|striped]] [[blue scarf|blue]] [[scarf]], a [[blue shirt|blue]] [[sleeveless shirt|sleeveless]] [[shirt]] that [[navel cutout|exposes the]] [[navel]], [[long sleeves|long]] [[white sleeves|white]][[two-tone sleeves|-and-]][[black sleeves|black]] [[detached sleeves]], a [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[blue skirt|blue]] [[miniskirt]], a [[bandaged leg|bandage]], and a [[vines|vine]] [[vine on leg|on her legs]], and [[blue footwear|blue]] [[toeless footwear|toeless]] [[boots]]. She fights with an [[axe]].

title: magnifying_glass
body:
A convex lens that is used to produce a magnified image of an object. The lens is usually mounted in a frame with a handle. A magnifying glass can be used to focus light, such as to concentrate the sun's radiation to create a hot spot at the focus for fire starting.

body:
Morrigna refers to three characters as a single entity which are based off "The Morrigan" from Irish mythology.

Badb wears white a white dress and has a two U-shaped hair ornaments.
Macha wears a red dress and has a rectangular shaped hair ornament.
Neamhan wears a blue dress and wears a headband that has a feather in the middle.
Refer to post #3524302

Umbrella tag for the three Characters in [[Shingeki no Bahamut]] and [[Granblue Fantasy]] who use [i]Morrigna[/i] as their collective title.

title: heliconia
body:
A genus of tropical [[flower]]ing plants in the family [i]Heliconiaceae[/i], with nearly 200 species native to tropical America and the western Pacific. Common names include [b]false bird of paradise[/b], [b]lobster claw[/b], [b]parakeet flower[/b], [b]parrot's beak[/b], and [b]wild plantain[/b].

The flowers of the genus can have various shapes, with inflorescences ranging from hanging to erect. Some species can resemble the [[bird of paradise flower]], but unlike the bird of paradise, heliconias produce several bracts (also known as spathe, a beak-like sheath that encloses the flowers) per stem. Bird of paradise, on the other hand, may only occasionally have a second spathe.

h4. Examples
* !asset #23380705: [i]Heliconia latispatha[/i]
* !asset #23380767: [i]Heliconia psittacorum[/i]
* !asset #23380703: [i]Heliconia rostrata[/i]
* !post #52137
* !post #521775: Hanging heliconia ([i]Heliconia rostrata[/i]) and bird of paradise

h4. Non-examples
* !asset #21572458: [[Bird of paradise flower]]
* !asset #23380637: [[Red ginger]]

h4. See also
* [[Anthurium]]
* [[Bird of paradise flower]]
* [[Red ginger (flower)|]]

h4. External links
* "Wikipedia: Heliconia":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heliconia
* "Wikipedia: Heliconia latispatha":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heliconia_latispatha
* "Wikipedia: Heliconia psittacorum":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heliconia_psittacorum
* "Wikipedia: Heliconia rostrata":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heliconia_rostrata

title: armitage_iii
body:
[b]Armitage III[/b] (アミテージ ザ サード, Amitēji za Sādo?) is a 1994 [[cyberpunk]] [[mecha]] anime series based around [[Naomi Armitage]], a highly advanced "Type-III" [[android]]. 
The title is a reference to [[Armitage]], character from the 80s science fiction novel [i][[Neuromancer]][/i].

The series began with the 4-part Original Video Animation [i]Armitage III[/i] and spawned two movies. 

The first film is a shortened version of the OVA entitled [i]Armitage III: Poly-Matrix[/i], redubbed in English. 

The second movie, [i]Armitage: Dual-Matrix[/i] is a sequel set some years after the original story.

title: energia_(rocket)
body:
Energia (Энергия, GRAU 11K25) was a super-heavy lift launch vehicle designed by NPO Energia in the 1980s under the Soviet [[Buran]] program. The vehicle consists of a large core stage powered by 4 RD-0120 engines and 4 liquid-fueled boosters each powered by a four-chamber RD-170 engine. Although the Energia itself only flew twice, the RD-180 engine derived from the RD-170 has flown successfully on over 100 launches of the American Atlas V launch vehicle.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Energia":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Energia_(rocket)]

title: joker_(2019)
body:
[b][i]Joker[/i][/b] is a 2019 American psychological thriller film directed and produced by Todd Phillips, who co-wrote the screenplay with Scott Silver. 

The film, based on [[DC Comics]] characters, stars Joaquin Phoenix as [[Joker (dc)|The Joker]] and provides a possible origin story for the character. 

Set in 1981, it follows [[Arthur Fleck]], a [spoilers]failed stand-up comedian whose descent into insanity and nihilism inspires a violent counter-cultural revolution against the wealthy in a decaying Gotham City.[/spoilers]

Joker premiered at the 76th Venice International Film Festival on August 31, 2019, where it won the Golden Lion, and was released in the United States on October 4, 2019. 

Joker became a major box office success and set records for an October release. It grossed over $1 billion, making it the first R-rated film to do so, the sixth-highest-grossing film of 2019, and the 31st-highest-grossing film of all time.

Joker received numerous accolades. At the 92nd Academy Awards, the film earned a leading 11 nominations, including Best Picture and Best Director, winning Best Actor for Phoenix and Best Original Score for female composer Hildur Guðnadóttir. Phoenix and Guðnadóttir also won at the Golden Globe and BAFTA Award ceremonies.

Joker was intended to be a standalone film with no sequels but Warner Bros. greenlit a follow-up project. [[Joker: Folie a Deux]], with Phoenix and Beetz reprising their roles and [[Lady Gaga]] joining as [[Harley Quinn]], was released on October 4, 2024.

title: help:image_source
body:
Sourcing images is important on Danbooru, for both archiving and tracking purposes, and is a mandatory process.

If you want to upload an image from the internet (such as from Pixiv, Twitter, etc) you can just copypaste the link onto the "upload page":/uploads/new and the site will automatically set the correct source.
Danbooru supports uploading from most art sites out there, so you should almost never need to save the file to disk before uploading it. See "here":/static/bookmarklet for a list of supported sites.

If you must upload from file (for example, because you can't find the original source), first reverse-search the file using "Saucenao":https://saucenao.com, "Ascii2D":https://ascii2d.net, or "Google Image Search":https://www.google.com/imghp, and upload from the right source instead if you are able to find it.

If you are uploading [[game cg]] that you ripped yourself, please write something that indicates so in the source field, such as "Extracted from the game", in order to tell approvers where your upload is from. If you're instead uploading it from a wiki or another similar source, you should still credit their original link in the source field.

If you are the commissioner or artist, you can tag your upload with [[commissioner upload]] or [[self-upload]] instead, because your version will likely be better than the publicly available versions. These two are the only cases where leaving the source empty is acceptable, although putting a note in the source field will help avoid ambiguity.

h6. List of Reverse Search Engines:

* "Saucenao":https://saucenao.com
* "Ascii2D":https://ascii2d.net
* "Google Image Search":https://www.google.com/imghp
* "Yandex":https://yandex.com/images/
* "TinEye":http://tineye.com/

h4. See also

* [[help:upload]]

* [[bad id]]
* [[md5 mismatch]]
* [[source request]]

title: wanjirou
body:
One of the two characters you can choose from in [[Mahjong Soul]]. He is an [[furry male|anthropomorphic]] [[dog boy]].

Together with [[Ichihime]], Wanjirou was one of the first characters to appear at the Mahjong Soul Shrine. After refusing to be bound by the mysterious duty entrusted to him, Wanjirou left the shrine in pursuit of freedom. title: raymond_stantz
body: Raymond Stantz, PhD, is a fictional character from the Ghostbusters franchise. He appears in the films [[Ghostbusters]] (1984), Ghostbusters II (1989), [[Casper (movie)]] (1995, as a cameo), Ghostbusters: Afterlife (2021) and Ghostbusters: Frozen Empire (2024), the animated television series [[The Real Ghostbusters]] and [[Extreme Ghostbusters]], and the video games Beeline's Ghostbusters, Ghostbusters: The Video Game (2009), Planet Coaster (2019), Ghostbusters: Spirits Unleashed (2022) and Ghostbusters: Rise of the Ghost Lord (2024). He was portrayed by Dan Aykroyd in five live action films, and voiced by Frank Welker in the animated series. He is a member of the Ghostbusters and one of the three Columbia University professors of parapsychology, along with Dr. [[Peter Venkman]] and Dr. [[Egon Spengler]].

title: ghostbusters
body:
[b]Ghostbusters[/b] is a 1984 American supernatural comedy film directed and produced by "Ivan Reitman":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ivan_Reitman and written by "Dan Aykroyd":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dan_Aykroyd and [[Harold Ramis]].

The film stars [[Bill Murray]], Aykroyd, and Ramis as three eccentric parapsychologists who start a ghost-catching business in New York City. [[Sigourney Weaver]] and "Rick Moranis":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rick_Moranis co-star as a client and her neighbor, and "Ernie Hudson":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ernie_Hudson as the Ghostbusters' first recruit.

Aykroyd conceived the film as a project for himself and fellow [[Saturday Night Live]] alumnus "John Belushi":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Belushi , with the "Ghostmashers" travelling through time and space. He and Ramis dramatically rewrote the script following Belushi's death and after Reitman deemed Aykroyd's initial vision financially impractical.

Ghostbusters was released in the United States on June 8, 1984. It was a critical and commercial success, receiving a positive response from critics and audiences and grossing US$242 million in the United States and more than $295 million worldwide. It was nominated for two Oscars at the 57th Academy Awards for Best Visual Effects and Best Original Song (for the eponymous theme song), but lost to Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom and The Woman in Red respectively. 

The film launched the Ghostbusters media franchise, which includes a 1989 sequel, [[Ghostbusters II]]; two animated television series, [[The Real Ghostbusters]] and [[Extreme Ghostbusters]] as well as several video games. 

A [[Ghostbusters (2016)|reboot]] starring Kristen Wiig, Melissa McCarthy, Kate McKinnon, and Leslie Jones was released in July 2016 but received negative reviews and was a box office bomb.

An official sequel to the original films titled Ghostbusters: Afterlife was released on November 19, 2021. A fourth film, Ghostbusters: Frozen Empire, was released on March 22, 2024.

title: ghostbusters_(2016)
body: Ghostbusters (also marketed as Ghostbusters: Answer the Call) is a 2016 American supernatural comedy film directed by Paul Feig, who co-wrote it with Katie Dippold. Starring Melissa McCarthy, Kristen Wiig, Kate McKinnon, Leslie Jones and [[Chris Hemsworth]], it is a reboot of the [[ghostbusters|1984 film of the same name]] and the third film in the Ghostbusters franchise. The story focuses on four eccentric women who start a ghost-catching business in [[New York City]] after a paranormal encounter.

Utilizing nuclear engineering, she designed and built their equipment, including the Proton Packs and Sidearms.

title: acguy
body:
A fictional manned military robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It first appeared in the [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] TV anime series from 1979.

[b]MSM-04 Acguy[/b]

One of [[Zeon]]'s earliest ampihibous [[mobile_suit|MS]] designs. The large-bodied Acguy possessed a powerful generator capable of driving a mega particle [[beam cannon]], aided by the fact that being underwater helped with cooling. It attained lasting fame for being oddly [[moe (phrase)|adorable]], usually being compared to [[beargguy|a teddy bear]] due to its round form and brown colors. [spoilers]Also because of its weirdly shaped head, which many an [[otaku]] thought looked like a [[dildo]], hence the popularity of the double entendre phrase [i]"Acguy is love"[/i].[/spoilers]

body:
A recurring character in the [i][[Ryuu ga Gotoku (series)|]][/i] series. 

She appears as a playable character in [i][[Ryuu ga Gotoku 5]][/i] but participates in rhythm game-based dance battles in contrast to the other protagonists.

Haruka is a girl who is taken into care by [[Kiryu Kazuma]] during the events of [i][[Ryuu ga Gotoku 1]][/i] and eventually becomes Kiryuu's adoptive daughter after the events of the game. She is a self-reliant mature girl for her age but still retains her childishness during her younger years.

body:
The recurring protagonist of the [i][[Ryuu ga Gotoku (series)|]][/i] series.

An ex-[[yakuza]] nicknamed the "Dragon of Dojima" because of his legendary achievements, Kiryuu is a stoic yet kind person who wants to live a normal life with his adoptive daughter, [[Sawamura Haruka]] alongside a group of children he helps take care of in an orphanage in [[Okinawa]].

Kiryu has a [[muscular]] build with slicked [[black hair]] and a [[goatee]], the outfit he usually wears consists of a [[grey suit]] and [[grey pants]] with [[red shirt]] underneath and [[white footwear|white shoes]].

title: saejima_taiga
body:
Playable character in the [i][[Ryuu Ga Gotoku (series)|]][/i] series.

He is a playable character in [i][[Ryuu Ga Gotoku 4]][/i] and [i][[Ryuu Ga Gotoku 5]][/i].

He is the oath brother of [[Majima Goro]] and dons a tattoo of a vicious [[tiger]]. Sajeima became a living legend after committing a 18-men massacre by himself. His fighting style relies on hard-hitting brute force that could even rival a bear in combat.

title: majima_goro
body:
A recurring character in the [i][[Ryuu ga Gotoku (series)|]][/i] series. 

He appears as a playable character in [i][[Ryuu ga Gotoku 0]][/i] and [i][[Ryuu ga Gotoku of The End]][/i].

As a [[yakuza]], Majima is a ferocious and unpredictable man; his infamous antics has resulted in people fearing him as "Mad Dog of Shimano." He is [[Saejima Taiga]]'s oath brother and is a frenemy to [[Kiryu Kazuma]].

Majima has a lean build, [[short hair|short]] [[black hair]] and a [[goatee]]. He wears an [[eyepatch]] with a snake pattern over his missing left eye. He is commonly depicted wearing an [[open clothes|open]] [[snake print|snakeskin]] blazer, a [[gold necklace]], [[black pants|black leather pants]] and [[black footwear|black steel-toed snakeskin shoes]]. His [[irezumi]] is a [[hannya]] surrounded by [[flower|flowers]] with two [[snake|snakes]] surrounding his arms.

Voiced by:

title: cyberknife
body:
A [[prototype design|scrapped]] [[Dream SMP]] character that was meant to be played by [[Technoblade]], but he was ultimately unable to. The plan was to have c!Technoblade leave for a training arc while Techno played Cyberknife on the updated Dream SMP world.

An "opposite" version of his main character with a blue color scheme. Capitalistic and loves government, somewhat similar to another character of Techno's, [[Sir Billiam III]].

Originally derived from a fan community meme about Technoblade's possible [[dark persona]] being his alternate Minecraft account he renamed to Cyberknife.

* !post #8240006: Officially-[[commission]]ed art of Cyberknife

According to the character's designer, [[Kloki (jester u)|]], he was intended to be a young, rich and arrogant character who potentially could have been directly related to Sir Billiam.

h4. External links

* "Philza discussing the original plans":https://youtube.com/watch?v=uFGwdTWLYgg

title: technoblade
body:
A [[Minecraft YouTube]]r, one of the most popular. He made content involving various PVP games demonstrating his skill in the game, and acquired a fanbase for his dry, snarky humor. He was a member of [[Dream SMP]], where he played the character of a militant anarchist fighting against tyranny, as well as [[Origins SMP]], where instead of his typical character, he played as a [[Technoblade (Bunny)|rabbit]] who was a carrot farmer.

He passed away from sarcoma in June 2022, but his legacy lives on in works created by his very passionate fans and charity work done by both his fans and co-workers in his honor.

Commonly associated with the phrases "Blood for the Blood God" and "Technoblade never dies".

h4. Appearance

His character is most commonly depicted as a [[pig boy]], either [[furry]] or simply a humanoid with animal ears. He is often portrayed as an [[androgynous]] man with long [[pink hair]], typically worn in a [[braid]]. His outfit typically consists of a [[red cape]] with a [[fur trim]], a [[white shirt]], [[pants]], a [[crown]], and [[boots]].

In [[Dream SMP]] fanart, he is often depicted alongside multiple dogs, a [[wither skull]], or given a single [[crystal earrings|emerald earring]] that matches his best friend [[Ph1LzA]].

He was recommended to Rhodes Island by Dr. [[Ceylon (arknights)|]], where he works as a battlefield and Logistics operator both.

Due to the decline of tourism in Siesta, he had to take many odd jobs to support his adoptive mother and siblings, one of which consisted of mining obsidian from the volcano, resulting in him contracting Oripathy.

His motif is based on the [[Japanese tit]], while his codename comes from the taxonomical name of a division of mosses.

title: endless_knot
body:
A type of "auspicious symbol". Several knots tied together; the complexity of the knot can vary, and it has a multitude of meanings.

Also known as the [i]infinity knot[/i]. In Hinduism, it's called the [i]Shrivatsa[/i].

It is an important symbol in Hinduism, Jainism and Buddhism. It's also an important cultural marker in places influenced by Tibetan Buddhism, such as Tibet, Mongolia, Tuva, Kalmykia, and Buryatia. It is also found in Celtic, Kazakh and Chinese symbolism.

Edless knots can be either [[celtic knot|celtic]] or [[chinese knot|chinese]].

The Chinese [[panchang knot]] is a type of endless knot. 
H4. Examples
* !asset #22916528: [tn]Source: "Adobe":[https://stock.adobe.com/se/search?k=chinese+knot&asset_id=316946840][/tn] Various types of endless knots

title: chinese_knot
body:
Lanyard-type arrangements where two cords enter from the top of the knot and two cords leave from the bottom. The knots are usually double-layered and symmetrical.

h4. Subtypes

* !post #7532017: [[Flower knot]]  [1]
* !asset #22916528: [tn]Source: "Adobe":[https://stock.adobe.com/se/search?k=chinese+knot&asset_id=316946840][/tn][[Endless knot]]  [2]
* !asset #22916276: [tn]Source: "Wikimedia":[https://https://commons.m.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:CiftIpteDugmeOnden.JPG#mw-jump-to-license][/tn] [[Button knot]]  [3]
* !asset #23359177: [tn]Source: "Wikimedia":[https://commons.m.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Pan_Chang_knot.jpg][/tn][[Panchang knot]]  [4]
* !asset #23360416: [tn]Source: "Wikimedia":[https://commons.m.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Good_luck_knot(ABOK_2437).jpg#mw-jump-to-license] [[Good luck Knot]] [5]

[1] [b][[Flower knot]][/b]
Any knot that has appears as if it has 'petals'. Also called clover knot.

[2] [b][[Endless knot]][/b]
An endless knot is a knot that appears continues throughout, having no opening or end point. There are many types and come in all sizes. The [[panchang knot]] is a type of endless knot. 

[3] [b][[Button Knot]][/b]
Tightly-woven design, no protruding loops. Present in both Chinese and Celtic imagery.

[4] [b][[Panchang Knot]][/b]
A type of [[endless knot]], can have varying amounts of rows, but always forms a tightly bound square.

[5] [b][[Good luck knot]][/b]
Similar to the [[panchang knot]], but only has two rows, always forms a square. 

h4.See also
* "Wikipedia article: Chinese knotting":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_knotting

title: good_luck_knot
body:
The good luck knot is a [[Chinese knot]] made up of two rows, giving the appearance of four squares. It can be turned into a pendant, often with a [[tassel]] In Korean its known as "Chrysanthemum knot" or "The lovers knot" 

For similar knots, but are made up of mire rows see [[panchang knot]].

title: lori_(napoleon_of_another_world!)
body: Secondary character of "[[Napoleon of Another World!]]". She is a minotaur and [[Daemon Haselworth|Daemon]]'s adoptive mother. Immature and a bit scatterbrained, she loves Daemon madly and worries about him constantly. Her maternal instinct leads her to shower everyone around her with attention.

title: tombow_mono
body:
MONO is a brand of products created by the company Tombow Pencil.

The MONO product featured most in anime and manga is a plastic eraser that comes in a case with blue, white, and black bars. 

In many posts, what you'll see is a [[brand name imitation]]. For example, the case might say "NONO" and the bars might be colored differently. 

h4. External links

* "MONO | TOMBOW PENCIL":[https://www.tombow.com/en/brands/mono/]

body:

title: heart_knot
body: There are many varieties of heart knot, but for tagging purposes use this tag to denote any knot made to look like a conventional heart (♡). The heart knot is a relatively modern knot so it does not appear to be a strictly a [[celtic knot|celtic]] or [[Chinese knot]].

title: panchang_knot
body:
A type of ([[Chinese knot|Chinese]]) [[Endless knot]], and one of the eight symbols of [[Buddhism]]. A symbol of good luck.

It can have a variety of "rows" , but it alwayd forms a square. 

For the Chinese knot with two "rows" see: [[Good luck knot]]
h4. Examples

h4. External links

title: fuzi
body:
A fuzi, also known as a fuchen, is a type of fly-whisk, consisting of a short staff with hair (from an animal such as a cow, horse, or yak) that is used as an instrument by Chan Buddhist monks and Taoist daoshi.

Originally used as a tool to shoo away flies from livestock without injuring them, it eventually came to be adopted by Buddhism and Taoism as it was perceived as having the power to sweep away desires and evil influences both in the environment of the holder and within their own thoughts, bringing them closer to enlightenment (in Buddhism) or transcending the mortal realm (in Taoism).
H4. See also
* [[flyswatter]]
h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Fuzi":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fuzi
